# Code owners for Seshat BI.
#
# GitHub requests review from these owners when a PR touches a matching path.
# NOTE: this is advisory until branch protection on `main` is configured to
# "Require review from Code Owners" (a GitHub repo setting, not a repo file).
#
# Later matches take precedence, so the security-critical paths are listed last.

# Default owner for everything.
*                                   @ahmed-shaaban-94

# Distributed source — what a `pip install seshat-bi` user executes.
/src/                               @ahmed-shaaban-94

# Supply chain: CI/release workflows run with repo tokens (release holds OIDC
# id-token:write). Any change here is security-sensitive.
/.github/workflows/                 @ahmed-shaaban-94
/.github/dependabot.yml             @ahmed-shaaban-94
/pyproject.toml                     @ahmed-shaaban-94

# Marketplace-distributed agent surface — these load into a consumer's agent,
# so an edit here can change what the agent is instructed to do. Review for
# prompt-injection and confidentiality (real client/company identifiers) before
# it ships to the Claude/Codex marketplaces.
/.claude-plugin/                    @ahmed-shaaban-94
/integrations/                      @ahmed-shaaban-94
/distribution/                      @ahmed-shaaban-94

# Security policy itself.
/SECURITY.md                        @ahmed-shaaban-94
